- 'Quality assurance passed' indicates that the product has met the required standards;
- 'Shipped' status means the order has been sent to the customer;
- 'Quantity range of '500/case'' refers to the specific packaging and quantity of the product;
- 'Order date' specifies the period during which the orders were placed.

- 'Passed quality assurance' indicates the product meets the required standards for sale;
- 'Delivered' status means the order has been successfully shipped and received by the customer;
- 'Total quantity sold' is the sum of the quantities ordered for each product;
- 'Average price per case' is the mean price per case across all delivered orders.

- "Total revenue" is the sum of all order amounts for a customer;
- "Average order value" is calculated by dividing the total revenue by the total number of orders;
- "Top 10 customers" refers to the customers with the highest total revenue.

- "top 10 most valuable customers" refers to the customers with the highest sales revenue;
- "garden of sales" is a metaphor for the sales environment or market;
- "flowers of revenue" is a metaphor for the sales revenue generated by customers;
- "bloom the brightest" indicates the highest or most significant revenue.

- "Top 10 customers" refers to the customers who have spent the most money in total;
- "Revenue-to-spending ratio" is calculated as the total revenue generated by the product divided by the total amount spent by the customer, rounded to two decimal places;
- "Products that shine the brightest" metaphorically refers to products that generate the highest revenue.

- 'reaped the most bountiful harvest' refers to the highest total revenue;
- 'accounting for the discounts they offered' means the total revenue is adjusted by the discount amount;
- The total revenue is calculated as the sum of (quantity * price per case * (1 - (discount amount / 100))).

- "Top 10 best-selling products" refers to the products with the highest total quantity sold;
- "Passed quality assurance" means the product has been verified to meet certain quality standards;
- "Priced in USD" indicates the currency of the product's price is US dollars.

- "Total spending" is the sum of all amounts spent by a customer across all their orders;
- The query includes all customers, even those who have not placed any orders, by using a `LEFT JOIN` and setting the total spent to 0 for such customers;
- The results are ordered by total spending in descending order to identify the top 10 customers.
